com.gfycat.core.downloading

Interface FeedManager


  • public interface FeedManager
    Responsible for downloading Gfycat items.

    • Method Detail

      • getCategories

        rx.Observable<GfycatCategoriesList> getCategories()
        Request categories list from cache. If none found, network request will be performed.

        If found in cache but expired - will return cached one and perform network request for updates

        Returns:
        Returns GfycatCategoriesList observable.

      • observeGfycats

        rx.Observable<FeedData> observeGfycats(android.content.Context context,
                                       FeedIdentifier feedIdentifier)
        Subscribe for Gfycat changes in local DB.

        !!! Important: You should NOT forget to unsubscribe, otherwise memory leak will occur.

        Parameters:
        feedIdentifier - - to subscribe for.
        Returns:
        Returns FeedData observable.

      • getGfycats

        rx.Completable getGfycats(FeedIdentifier feedIdentifier)
        Perform a network request of Gfycat list for a specified . FeedData containing this request result will be returned via observeGfycats(Context, FeedIdentifier) observable.

        Parameters:
        feedIdentifier - - to get gfycats for.
        Returns:
        Returns Completable calling onError in case of failure or onComplete in case of success.

      • getNewGfycats

        rx.Completable getNewGfycats(FeedDescription feedDescription)
        Perform a network request of new Gfycats for a specified . FeedData containing this request result will be returned via observeGfycats(Context, FeedIdentifier) observable.

        NOTE: This works only with FeedDescription obtained via PublicFeedIdentifier.trending().

        Parameters:
        feedDescription - from the latest FeedData received with observeGfycats(Context, FeedIdentifier)
        Returns:
        Returns Completable calling onError in case of failure or onComplete in case of success.

      • getMoreGfycats

        rx.Completable getMoreGfycats(FeedDescription feedDescription)
        Perform a network request of more Gfycats for corresponding feed. Will download Gfycats and save to local DB if needed.

        FeedData containing this request result will be returned via observeGfycats(Context, FeedIdentifier) observable.

        Parameters:
        feedDescription - from latest FeedData received with observeGfycats(Context, FeedIdentifier).
        Returns:
        Returns Completable calling onError in case of failure or onComplete in case of success

      • getGfycat

        rx.Single<Gfycat> getGfycat(String gfyId)
        Look for a Gfycat in cache. Request one from network, if not found.
        Returns:
        Returns Single emitting a Gfycat object or null, if not found neither in cache nor during network request.
